                            <comment id="14034807" author="myrna" created="Wed, 18 Jun 2014 05:44:41 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Adding a number of extra checks to EnvTest.&lt;br/&gt;
Also adding output in case we run with the textui.TestRunner.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Review/input will be appreciated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14034811" author="myrna" created="Wed, 18 Jun 2014 05:47:00 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Is there a way to check for Profile 2 (JEP 161) support?&lt;br/&gt;
Or will a combination of having JDBC 4.2 but no JNDI support imply this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14035684" author="knutanders" created="Wed, 18 Jun 2014 14:25:55 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I think a mechanism to determine the profile was intentionally left out, so that applications would be encouraged to check for the functionality they actually need rather than the profile. I suppose that was done in order to allow moving to more fine-grained modules later without changing the applications.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
